author: CNN
description: In a "60 Minutes" interview, President Donald Trump said that he doesn't know who Changpeng Zhao is, the Binance co-founder and crypto tycoon he recently pardoned. Zhao, known as CZ, pleaded guilty to a money laundering charge in 2023. #CNN #News
title: Trump claims he doesn't know Binance billionaire he pardoned

author: CNN
description: While campaigning for New Jersey Democratic gubernatorial candidate Rep. Mikie Sherrill, Former President Barack Obama had a playful exchange after being interrupted by an excited supporter. “I mean, you look cute. But I am married. Michelle’s fine too,” Obama joked. #cnn #news #obama
title: ‘You look cute’: Obama jokes with a supporter

author: CNN
description: In an interview with CNN's Elex Michaelson, Speaker Emerita Nancy Pelosi criticized President Trump's actions, stating he's the president, but "doesn't honor the Constitution" and is the "worst thing on the face of the Earth." Watch Pelosi's full interview with Michaelson on "The Story Is with Elex Michaelson" at 9p PT 12aET.
title: Nancy Pelosi calls Donald Trump a 'vile creature'

author: CNN
description: Key elections come as a new poll shows the Democratic Party holds a sizable enthusiasm advantage as views of Trump dip further into negative territory. #CNN #News
title: Polling: Trump approval at second-term low amid key elections

author: CNN
description: Video from Oregon’s Department of Justice shows what they claim is federal officers using force on protesters outside the US Immigration and Customs Enforcement building in Portland. CNN has reached out to the Department of Homeland Security for comment.
title: Trial evidence appears to show agents tackle Portland protesters

author: CNN
description: The olive harvest in the occupied West Bank has become a season of fear. Brutal settler attacks have marred what should be a time of history, culture and tradition. More than 200 attacks have occurred within the last month, according to the Palestinian Authority, often with the army’s support. The Israeli military told CNN it “recognizes the importance of the olive harvest in maintaining the fabric of life in the region,” but acknowledged it has restricted entry to certain areas in order to “prevent friction.” CNN’s Jeremy Diamond visits a Palestinian farm damaged by settlers and speaks to a farmer attacked by a settler and Israeli soldiers while trying to reach his family’s olive groves.
title: Palestinian olive pickers attacked over and over

author: CNN
description:
The Trump administration said Monday that it will provide only half of the normal food stamp benefits for November by tapping into the program’s contingency fund amid the government shutdown. But recipients are not likely to see the payments immediately. Some $4.65 billion from the Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program’s contingency fund will “be obligated to cover 50% of eligible households’ current allotments” for November, according to a sworn statement from a US Department of Agriculture official submitted in federal court.

CNN's Alayna Treene reports from the White House, and Brianna Keilar speaks with Rep. Sarah McBride (D-DE). #CNN #News
title: Trump administration will provide only half of usual food stamp benefits in November

author: CNN
description: While trekking through the rubble of a demolished home, CNN's David Culver met a 4-year-old boy who survived Hurricane Melissa by sheltering in the closet.
title: Boy survives Hurricane Melissa in closet

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump said he has “no idea” who Changpeng Zhao is, the founder of the world’s largest cryptocurrency exchange, Binance.  CNN’s Jake Tapper breaks down the connection the president’s family has to Zhao. #cnn #news #binance #shorts
title: Analysis: Tapper breaks down Trump’s connection to Binance CEO he pardoned

author: CNN
description: Officials at George Bush Intercontinental Airport in Houston are telling passengers that TSA checkpoint lines could stretch three hours due to staffing shortages from the ongoing government shutdown. CNN's Pete Muntean reports. #CNN #News
title: Massive lines at Houston airport as shutdown continues

author: CNN
description: While addressing a packed crowd on the eve of the election, New Jersey Republican gubernatorial nominee Jack Ciattarelli was surprised by a visit from his son, Jack, who had been serving in Kuwait with the US Army. #CNN #politics #election
title: NJ candidate gets surprise visit from son

author: CNN
description: Flight delays linked to the ongoing federal government shutdown continue, with this past weekend marking the worst for air traffic control staffing shortages since the shutdown began, according to a CNN analysis of Federal Aviation Administration operations plans. #CNN #News
title: Worst weekend for air traffic controller staffing since start of shutdown

author: CNN
description: President Trump appeared on “60 Minutes” Sunday night, one year after suing the CBS show over the editing of a Kamala Harris interview — and he was well aware that his answers would similarly be trimmed for time. CNN chief media analyst Brian Stelter reports  #CNN #News
title: Trump spent 90 minutes with ‘60 Minutes’ — here’s what happened

author: CNN
description: While vacationing with her family in Montego Bay, Jamaica, Fizza Najarali found herself caught in Hurricane Melissa. She used TikTok to document the storm in real time, sharing footage of the destruction and evacuation process. #CNN #news
title: Tourist documents Hurricane Melissa on TikTok

author: CNN
description: Carlos Manzo knew speaking out against organized crime made him a target. Then he was shot dead during a Day of the Dead festival. His murder has become another grim example of the growing danger facing local leaders across Mexico. #cnn #dayofthedead #mexico
title: Mayor who spoke out against cartels shot dead

author: CNN
description:
US President Donald Trump wrote on social media that he has ordered the Defense Department to prepare for possible military action in Nigeria as he continues to accuse the nation of not doing enough to stem violence against Christians — an accusation Nigeria has repeatedly denied.

Sara Sidner speaks with CNN's Fareed Zakaria, and Erica Hill speaks with CNN international diplomatic editor Nic Robertson. #CNN #News
title: Trump orders Pentagon to 'prepare for possible action' in Nigeria

author: CNN
description: Fighting for control of the strategic hub of Pokrovsk in eastern Ukraine is intensifying, with the Russian Defense Ministry claiming to have eliminated a group of Ukrainian special forces sent to help defend the area. Retired Air Force Col. Cedric Leighton shares his take on the state of the war.  #CNN #News
title: Retired colonel reacts to intensified frontline fighting in Ukraine

author: CNN
description: A medieval tower in Rome partially collapsed twice, with one worker hospitalized, Reuters reports. The 13th century tower has been in disuse for years and was undergoing restoration. #CNN #news
title: Tower in Rome partially collapses

author: CNN
description: On the last full day of campaigning before Tuesday's election day, candidates in Virginia, New York City and New Jersey are making their final push. CNN chief data analyst Harry Enten runs the numbers. Also, CNN's Kate Bolduan speaks with Larry Sabato, director of the Center for Politics at the University of Virginia. CNN senior reporter Edward-Isaac Dovere reports on the differing approaches Democrats are taking in Virginia and New York City. #CNN #News
title: The first big electoral test of Trump's 2nd term: Harry Enten runs the numbers

title: Trump’s approval rating hits new low for second term

description: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un inspected his elite “Storm Corps” troops, reportedly sent to fight alongside Russian forces in Ukraine. He praised their “matchless fighting spirit” in a state-TV show of force that took place the same day China’s leader Xi Jinping met South Korea’s leader Lee Jae Myung.
title: State TV shows elite North Korean soldiers

title: 6.3 magnitude quake rocks Afghanistan

description:
CNN reporter Camila DeChalus speaks to federal workers lining up at So What Else, a food bank in the Washington, DC, area. They have a clear message for Congress.

#CNN #News
title: 'We have to choose to feed ourselves or pay the bills’: Federal workers line up at food bank

description: Video shows federal agents repeatedly striking a man on the ground in a Chicago suburb. The Department of Homeland Security says the agents were conducting an immigration enforcement operation at the time.
title: Federal agents strike man pinned to the ground during enforcement act
